## What I Am Still Thinking About

Something I want to understand better is how the shared responsibility model changes depending on which AWS services you use. Today I focused on Infrastructure as a Service — EC2 instances where the customer manages the operating system. But AWS also offers managed services like RDS for databases and Elastic Beanstalk for application deployment, where AWS takes on more of the responsibility for underlying components.

Does using more managed services shift more responsibility to AWS and reduce the customer's security burden? In some ways yes — but it also introduces new questions about vendor trust and about what the customer can and cannot directly control or inspect. I want to think more carefully about where the right balance is for an OpenMRS deployment as this project develops.

